article.headline: Lavender's 18 points lead way as Ohio State cruises
article.linkText: Lavender-led Ohio St. blows out Cleveland St.
article.story:
COLUMBUS, Ohio -- Jantel Lavender had 18 points and Ashlee Trebilcock and Brittany Johnson added 12 each to lead Ohio State (No. 17 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) to a 68-54 victory over Cleveland State on Monday night.

Kailey Klein had 22 of her 30 points in the second half for Cleveland State, who trailed 38-18 at halftime.

Ohio State (8-2) held the Vikings without a field goal for nearly 9 minutes to increase a seven-point lead to 44-18 before Stephaine Crosley hit a jumper for the Vikings (4-5) with 17:11 left.

The Buckeyes' largest lead was 56-26 with 12 minutes left, but Cleveland State whittled it to 59-41 on a field goal by Klein 5 minutes later. Ohio State got a 3 from Cherise Daniels and a field goal from Trebilcock to return the lead to 23 before the Vikings made a run in the final 3 minutes.

Both teams were coming off nine-day breaks.
